  "body": "<!--üíéüíéüíéüíéüíéüíéüíéüíéüíéüíéüíéüíéüíéüíéüíéüíéüíéüíéüíéüíéüíéüíéüíéüíéüíéüíéüíéüíéüíéüíé\r\n\r\nHellooo! üòÑ \r\n\r\nTo help us tend to your issue faster, please search our currently open issues before submitting a new one.\r\nExisting issues often contain information about workarounds, resolution, or progress updates.\r\n\r\nüíéüíéüíéüíéüíéüíéüíéüíéüíéüíéüíéüíéüíéüíéüíéüíéüíéüíéüíéüíéüíéüíéüíéüíéüíéüíéüíéüíéüíéüíéüíéüíéüíéüíéüíé-->\r\n\r\n# üêû Bug Report\r\n\r\n### Description\r\n\r\nWhen requesting `/eth/v1/validator/duties/sync/<epoch>` around the beginning of the requested epoch (first 6-12 seconds or so), Prysm returns a 500 error. This happens on both prater & mainnet. Not sure if it's consistent, but it's reproducible on most prater epochs.\r\n\r\n### Has this worked before in a previous version?\r\n\r\n<!-- Did this behavior use to work in the previous version? -->\r\n<!-- ‚úçÔ∏è--> Yes, the previous version in which this bug was not present was: v2.1.4\r\n\r\n## üî¨ Minimal Reproduction\r\n\r\n<!--\r\nPlease let us know how we can reproduce this issue. Include the exact method you used to run Prysm along with any flags used in your beacon chain and/or validator. Make sure you don't upload any confidential files or private keys.\r\n-->\r\n\r\n## üî• Error\r\n\r\n\r\nReproduce:\r\n1. Wait for the first slot of epoch X\r\n2. `POST /eth/v1/validator/duties/sync/<X>` with a JSON array of validator indices (in my case ~2500 indices)\r\n3. Try again if it succeeds (there's a short window of a few seconds  at the beginning of the epoch)\r\n\r\nResponse:\r\n\r\n```json\r\n{\"message\":\"Could not get sync committee state: requested slot number is higher than head slot number\",\"code\":500}\r\n```\r\n\r\n\r\n## üåç  Your Environment\r\n\r\n**Operating System:**\r\n\r\n<pre>\r\n  <code>\r\nUbuntu 22.04\r\n  </code>\r\n</pre>\r\n\r\n**What version of Prysm are you running? (Which release)**\r\n\r\n<pre>\r\n  <code>\r\nv3.0.0\r\n  </code>\r\n</pre>\r\n\r\n**Anything else relevant (validator index / public key)?**\r\n\r\n",
